{"title":"BRAUNWALD. 1. Consideraciones generales","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Estudios Pivotales/BRAUNWALD. 1. Consideraciones generales-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Consideraciones generales","guid":"FNE6FhvLoaBC8GKI9Hb_uA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Repercusión\\Nglobal de las ECV","guid":"__aZqeFGNeXPon5XosavfA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Desplazamiento de la repercusión:","guid":"8w4BMhZmfUIIR5F2LPfRjA","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• ECV: principal causa de muerte mundial desde 2013.","guid":"xrzI35NbpqHVMnWAYNbbPw","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• 17,3 M muertes (2013) → 32% total global.","guid":"_Yoh3YAnp9LDsGd623_tVw","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"• 330 M AVAD perdidos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"2","text":"• Incremento en países de renta media y baja (PRMB)\\N⬆️ ECV en cifras absolutas (4-5x más muertes vs PRA).","guid":"_pz_OK0wS79eCtYDUrxdIg","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Transiciones\\Nepidemiológicas:","guid":"Qg8sdI_neS0VwbPCa2X0fg","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Plagas y hambrunas: predominan infecciones y malnutrición.","guid":"WhnZT5vd5AoGkERYzx9OvA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Mortalidad elevada en lactantes, ⬇️ esperanza de vida (~30 años).","guid":"ReTi1b22kbJl1HkDOzvmZg","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"• Pandemias en disminución: mejoras en salud pública → ⬇️ infecciones, ⬆️ esperanza de vida.","guid":"hKbGve0k4b9R14EbV6ZHDg","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"7","text":"• ECV ligadas a hipertensión y ACV > CI.","guid":"v335o5N56JQvvNRzYxEKjQ","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"7","text":"• Enfermedades degenerativas y causadas por el hombre: ⬆️ ingesta calórica, ⬇️ actividad física → aterosclerosis.","guid":"BYL9AcUpjdBDTT6u0_9ulA","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"7","text":"• ECV: CI y ACV predominantes.","guid":"0cmbhO1ILy4idbeSSrJ57Q","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"7","text":"• Enfermedades degenerativas demoradas: ⬇️ mortalidad por ECV (edad ajustada) gracias a avances terapéuticos.","guid":"M6dQxwfDDsx4gKI7jrWWqQ","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"7","text":"• CI y ACV siguen como principales causas de muerte.","guid":"G_JsdHNFiFzYGJJ0hufX5A","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"1","text":"Variaciones actuales en la\\Nrepercusión global:","guid":"ETGOAewCpcoJYktb1gPs3w","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• PRA: 38% muertes por ECV.","guid":"o16aQEziWnQFwvDXDglInQ","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"• Europa oriental: 59%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"16","text":"• África subsahariana: 12%.","guid":"Ti4vkgGtpiloyD07YbFOJw","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"1","text":"Factores de\\Nriesgo (ECV):","guid":"7UBPJgxku1Cv-ElqW8gzlA","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Tabaco 🚬","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Hipertensión ⬆️📊","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"• Lípidos ⬆️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"• Diabetes 🍬","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"20","text":"• Obesidad 🏋️ ♂️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"20","text":"• Inactividad física 🛋️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"20","text":"• Dieta 🍽️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"20","text":"• Envejecimiento 👴","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"1","text":"Era de la inactividad\\Ny obesidad:","guid":"JZhprQCaOIu8lcxvSWWnWw","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Epidemia de obesidad → ⬆️ diabetes tipo 2, hipertensión.","guid":"g7AWU3931csPTXGRJV9J9w","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Reducción en tabaquismo y control de colesterol en PRA.","guid":"ozTgQtFDbYThiywTc5lflw","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV ajustada por edad ⬇️ 3% anual en las últimas décadas.","guid":"0UrzEtdOA8tE0ucJgOY_Lg","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"1","text":"Repercusiones\\Neconómicas:","guid":"SCu4IxktdIWm8uYbRcHWEw","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• ECV impactan significativamente en los PRMB.","guid":"qOlhnN99HejLOqtKAggedw","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"• Estrategias de prevención y tratamiento, como el control de la\\Nhipertensión y las estatinas, han reducido las muertes.","guid":"gVUJbty7m7xWwgNUh1i_yQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"1","text":"Soluciones rentables:","guid":"oh0SshedqlHs1cHR9TbRug","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"• Tratamiento de ECV establecida.","guid":"o9drcio1X2MpTjTlAHeZFQ","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"36","text":"• Evaluación de riesgo poblacional.","guid":"UBzqVl4Cw3TreVho_26MCQ","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"36","text":"• Intervenciones comunitarias y políticas de salud pública.","guid":"kkMftWzhCFaYbvPFx88WWg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"0","text":"Variaciones actuales en la\\Nrepercusión global de las ECV","guid":"Hx4IEjdRgFV5kGeRDzTpuQ","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"Factores que influyen\\Nen la repercusión:","guid":"xFMxWla25FQIkALbYZuV1A","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"1. Crecimiento poblacional ⬆️ número total de muertes por ECV.","guid":"9nvd7SyvQ344k-3JdFEZVQ","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"2. Envejecimiento poblacional ⬆️ proporción de muertes por ECV.","guid":"APBbLTsBVObs5-k1ILwfUA","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"41","text":"3. Mejora en prevención y tratamiento ⬇️ tasas de mortalidad ajustadas por edad.","guid":"Rg_yj_kxMCh_WmJFYsKsDA","children":[]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"40","text":"Datos Global Burden of\\NDisease (GBD) 2013:","guid":"M2hWgb99MQmxRBjRPpPX3Q","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"• Aumento de muertes por ECV (1990-2013): +46%.","guid":"DFqn5aAuyv2E2Amu25rkgw","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"• CI: 15% de muertes globales.","guid":"qlrVgbbneSET1r8LyVAeHg","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"• Ictus: 12% (50% isquémico, 50% hemorrágico).","guid":"iXU1e2TB0UH5HU3_OZzK6w","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"45","text":"• 14,5 M muertes por CI e ictus (2013) → 25% de muertes globales.","guid":"VzVk7E5UC5dnjSrK1SZvLg","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"40","text":"Tendencias en tasas de\\Nmortalidad ajustadas por edad:","guid":"S8Jy_GAr1s3gVatpCZgq4w","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Reducción global (1990-2013): -21,9%.","guid":"j3jaLKckkDXXog5JMIHsCg","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"• 1990: 374/100.000 hab. ⬇️ 2013: 292/100.000 hab.","guid":"pzlu7LUvDcP-t8PKJA95pw","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"• Regiones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"• Asia oriental, Europa, Latinoamérica: ⬇️ mortalidad ajustada por ECV.","guid":"KliyZSjdlRyZLT5X7L6KUw","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"• África subsahariana: pocos cambios.","guid":"_1RGkBCknxcPaau7afrXfw","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"• Asia meridional: ⬆️ significativa en mortalidad ajustada.","guid":"ffNLrdwTVeaSuWnsp0UR8Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"40","text":"Variaciones\\Nsegún ingreso:","guid":"QfYa8V-9BV8ZZqBaR2gwpA","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• PRMB:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"• Tendencias: ⬆️ mortalidad ajustada por ECV (340 → 390/100.000 hab.).","guid":"h4L5ifJli_c5nYJ9weLUiQ","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"• Reducción posterior: 432 ⬇️ 400/100.000.","guid":"SFUxFckW0yJeYarn4YI-dA","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"57","text":"• PRA:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• Reducción significativa: 330 ⬇️ 202/100.000 (-37%).","guid":"oTurzcfuX8nUwd7CJLSQdA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"40","text":"Diferencias regionales\\Nen ECV:","guid":"nXqYXXbhbS0Zldq6YyK_2A","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"• Asia oriental, África subsahariana: predominio del ACV sobre CI.","guid":"z5bn5ZkLEQasD24teFwIlA","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"• Cardiopatía hipertensiva: principal causa de morbimortalidad en algunas regiones.","guid":"I846-Vlj5pHt_c-LhvA-0Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"40","text":"Factores\\Nadicionales:","guid":"rFFquyFkG5zHpRIJl9kQUw","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"• Diferencias culturales y genéticas → variabilidad en riesgo de ECV.","guid":"u4hKYWnvJtnp8pWeh-0RGA","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"66","text":"• Consumo de grasas saturadas: India ⬆️ vs. China.","guid":"eDcq59NnuOMMWjZxFSROJA","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"66","text":"• Impacto de guerras y enfermedades infecciosas (VIH/sida): África subsahariana.","guid":"IWkSPJcaYhKVAW1vqUxVfg","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"40","text":"Desigualdad\\Nsocioeconómica:","guid":"vCuuvicg7lMI_laSLF2f1w","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"• PRMB: CI afecta a población más joven → mayor mortalidad en personas activas.","guid":"BGoUGiYyTvMP2itCntBawQ","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"• Grupos socioeconómicos más desfavorecidos ⬆️ tasas de CI y factores de riesgo.","guid":"ez9mhDIuWftgs-uwnTdqxw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"0","text":"Variaciones actuales en la\\Nrepercusión global de las ECV","guid":"VYYi9x26Ng8PMil_ZaZh4g","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Asia oriental y Pacífico","guid":"VZ7LOmcgbPcP3ITASV7_Ww","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013): 38% del total de muertes.","guid":"Za_YvxWqMoMbduVoSatMJA","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"• CI: 31% ⬇️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"• ACV: 50% ⬆️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"74","text":"• Tendencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"• Aumento de CI (+40%) y ACV (+18%) entre 1990-2010.","guid":"RW_3yCg4IcQ_vCj-XJlCPA","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"• Japón: Reducción de mortalidad por ECV (-60% desde 1960). CI baja, pero ACV alta.","guid":"KmyBMh7VwmlSJlBgMY6E6A","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"78","text":"• Factores protectores: dieta baja en grasas, pescado, vegetales.","guid":"e6q2Q1bvWbUWIpWQXQ2pfw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"73","text":"Europa central,\\Noriental y Asia central","guid":"CTc-KSjgth9NqohNZXALlQ","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"• Europa oriental: 793/100.000 ⬆️","guid":"Nk7TlhzzsSQ3acxxFAwcVw","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"• Europa central: 547/100.000","guid":"QU2BniN03DFOo4vXFuxM2A","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"82","text":"• CI: principal causa de muerte (55% de muertes).","guid":"CpVJKF6AEJhgS0wzcEUh5w","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"82","text":"• Alta mortalidad en población laboral (45-69 años).","guid":"dCpDG3vCMZs58G4LOZo64w","children":[]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"73","text":"Latinoamérica y\\NCaribe (LAC)","guid":"I_pTX3mslwoWM30fTmbUkg","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013): 29% del total de muertes.","guid":"GIJZc2hZzYB_9Vl6FC0Ptg","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"• CI: 14% ⬇️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"• ACV: 6.9% ⬇️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"88","text":"• Tendencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Reducción en Argentina, Chile y Uruguay.","guid":"P0knNRYX7wtxOrk2SIBlXw","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"• Aumento en el Caribe y Centroamérica.","guid":"PvilKj7lQYMt8HD0dUd4wQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"73","text":"África septentrional y\\NOriente Medio","guid":"W9jyp2VaPWUJU5UYHSZ0RQ","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013): 42% del total de muertes.","guid":"CM8Zllf3IO80EsEdE2Rivw","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"• CI: 9% ⬇️ marginalmente desde\\N1990.","guid":"NncxhxReDVADqYSmKqF0og","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"• ACV: 32%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"95","text":"• Tasa global: 180/100.000","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"95","text":"• AVAD perdidos (2013):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"• CI: 9.7 millones.","guid":"ECA-6z2Z8rJkO6-FNBqSSg","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"• ACV: 5.7 millones.","guid":"N0aJvHpvLKUCgWbcT8jjLw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"73","text":"Asia meridional","guid":"Ysj6JQJ2wFdj9fLlIhIhWg","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013): 27% del total de muertes.","guid":"GI6vYlUwrBtqkoa5V4dUjA","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"103","text":"• CI: 15% (2 M muertes).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"103","text":"• ACV: 6.8% (30% de ECV).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"103","text":"• India: CI más prevalente en hombres y zonas urbanas.","guid":"FBXtnhiC961Mzs1Nb-7gRQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"73","text":"África subsahariana","guid":"fd01E1YiYmUNFVSKBqxOqQ","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"• Mortalidad por ECV (2013):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"• África occidental: 7.5%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"• África meridional: 13% ⬆️","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"108","text":"• Mortalidad menor que la media global, pero aumento en África meridional.","guid":"LhmDVUEoFacaELFoZJC03A","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"0","text":"Factores de\\Nriesgo de ECV","guid":"RwqJt0K55cogEOYCNOePYA","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"Principales factores\\Nmodificables:","guid":"W1QowXNt2QQZwPQtEpqyfQ","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"1. PA alta: 54% CI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"2. Colesterol elevado: 32% CI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"3. Obesidad/sobrepeso: 18%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"4. Ingesta alimentaria: 67%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"114","text":"5. Tabaco: 18%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"113","text":"Tabaquismo","guid":"bd0FqRxCWwliY5WsUKX_zg","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"• Prevalencia mundial: 1.300 M fumadores (2014).","guid":"XvxA0wJ0e64FjY8vfbVcNA","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"• PRMB: 80% del consumo global.","guid":"SM4EP3hFsFg0_Sb2ZFg47A","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"120","text":"• Mayor prevalencia en Kiribati (71% H, 42,9% M).","guid":"VZBYOkPMRkUT-Fs4S133yg","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"120","text":"• China: 301 M fumadores (50% H).","guid":"H2oy4jOHXck_CMxtUSqB5A","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"120","text":"• PRMB: Tabaco mayor causa prevenible de muerte (>1.000 M fallecimientos en s. XXI).","guid":"YCu05Dlf77oxBFQ7Tfghpw","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"120","text":"• Fumadores pasivos: 600.000 muertes anuales (2011).","guid":"TcfEb3Vu224RSrFif-nPMw","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"120","text":"• Prohibiciones de tabaco → ⬇️ SCA (Irlanda -12%).","guid":"SQuMITpDov8NYAK4EBYV2A","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"113","text":"Hipertensión","guid":"HrkbYEZZiJFyuCEpN0fKwg","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"• PA alta (sistólica > 115 mmHg):","guid":"fP2IyS1w6LpE_aU4W_nJnA","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"• 62% ACV","guid":"L-VkaEqLNGdZryXQeLNopw","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"• 49% CI","guid":"QtDkvw6sTMddC6GUGGE8-g","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"• 7 M muertes/año.","guid":"UniTDHED_MxjvzTEceLF7g","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"128","text":"• Prevalencia hipertensión no\\Ncontrolada:","guid":"JItalSLIATJDDUfSBLcPeQ","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"• 1980: 605 M → 2008: 978 M","guid":"XCfw7HQRnA1SrzEhKe-1Ww","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"• Mayor prevalencia: África oriental (Mozambique, Níger) y Europa oriental.","guid":"aYB3fGP54oMp2YSOMowDnQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"128","text":"• Descenso PA en PRA: ⬇️ 2,4 mmHg/década en hombres, ⬇️ 3,1 mmHg en mujeres.","guid":"Hj2Fgjc5h0ZCohl1GzsOSw","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"113","text":"Lípidos","guid":"G4o0rV1Kp-IOzx9PL6AiSw","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"• Colesterol elevado:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"• 56% CI","guid":"ZKpwAAefvq13NNfnFI_UaA","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"• 18% ACV","guid":"UirzFVDj_bgNQz0PFPvX1A","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"• Disminución en PRA, aumento en PRMB (China, India, Brasil).","guid":"X5BKf2pO3qMtXRTOMgjdiw","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"138","text":"• África subsahariana: niveles más bajos.","guid":"W1LbbxEcSZMj66N6f942BA","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"• Concentraciones\\Nmedias globales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"• H: 4,64 mmol/L (179,6 mg/dl)","guid":"M-RKxWb460wElUV-EAw7sQ","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"• M: 4,76 mmol/L (184,2 mg/dl)","guid":"WwqHWldEdp85-_EMRIr-1g","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"137","text":"• Descensos significativos: Europa central y Asia central.","guid":"Oz5ZImPVdZp3FwJzWXvepA","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"113","text":"Diabetes","guid":"dc2fkFud7JwfjwKRc6rUow","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"• Prevalencia: 346 M personas con diabetes (2011).","guid":"Gw784Dm5G-h0tuzvf7ls4A","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"• PRMB: 80% de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"• Mayor prevalencia: Oriente Medio, África septentrional (12,5%).","guid":"QVjalWvrxNYUSUFIE4PNqg","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"• India, China: mayores poblaciones diabéticas (61,3 M, 90 M).","guid":"PM_CjiGMflcof6V_HGANDQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"147","text":"• Asociación con obesidad visceral.","guid":"C9tc-1Xcuk1OaOqZZy44ag","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"113","text":"Obesidad","guid":"McBPAiykVxt6VyNMX9nSVw","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"• Aumento global: 1.460 M adultos con sobrepeso, 502 M obesos (2008).","guid":"ZvkD4HJUjhNnDG5vGt1OpQ","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"• PRMB: incremento acelerado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"• IMC global: ⬆️ 0,4 kg/m²/década en hombres, ⬆️ 0,5 kg/m² en mujeres.","guid":"WU15X2uhs-0q6YpWNFgAuQ","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"• Mayor incremento: Oceanía (1,3 kg/m² H, 1,8 M).","guid":"QuYqjGTle2J44v-PfiSDrg","children":[]}]},{"id":"158","parent":"113","text":"Dieta","guid":"bcxswxRn1LVEaoczQ1KPug","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"• Transición nutricional: mayor consumo de grasas animales y aceites vegetales procesados → ⬆️ riesgo de CI.","guid":"SLrw_G_6AgJXoGJSY8nt3A","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"158","text":"• Ejemplo: China: aumento en grasas del 25% al 35% (1982-2002).","guid":"KbMd6kxXT0Fjg1q8awv4gA","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"113","text":"Inactividad física","guid":"MiIKxFOcsLIo-PGdDXYzhQ","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"• PRA: prevalencia alta de inactividad física.","guid":"OEMUF3fMnAR-j8YqdRLWpg","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"• Recomendación: 30 min ejercicio moderado 5 días/semana.","guid":"GVkaXCcPa6kRcuOzJTR3Vw","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"161","text":"• Crisis cubana: aumento de actividad física → ⬇️ IMC (-1,5 unidades).","guid":"fOwl91_bzkwMYq_BY-Up1w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"0","text":"Repercusiones\\Neconómicas de la CI","guid":"UjBcX3NvHjB-wnh9K33Vvw","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"1. Coste directo en el\\Nsistema sanitario:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"• Estudios de coste de\\Nenfermedad incluyen:","guid":"XxDSHSmsAtNf1dZ4Ifb8qQ","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"• IM, angina, insuficiencia cardíaca (IC) atribuible a CI.","guid":"DpF-Nli41gggG4BXV0xvMg","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"167","text":"• Intervenciones (trombolíticos, ICP, cateterismo).","guid":"SLLYCne74qk7Fl0PcmX19Q","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"167","text":"• Tratamiento ambulatorio y prevención secundaria.","guid":"RBMx6h6Zt8tdce51fFZGAg","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"167","text":"• Residencias, rehabilitación, atención domiciliaria.","guid":"FmZT0FwBtJ9xaRyoL79uLA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"165","text":"2. Impacto familiar por\\Nepisodios catastróficos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"• Desembolsos altos → pérdida de ahorros/venta de propiedades.","guid":"AxEgSQLcAFtU8-WDf_1GQA","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"172","text":"• PRMB: falta de cobertura generalizada → 150 M personas/año sufren catástrofe económica por gastos médicos.","guid":"YrfOqGFWlURj4nAXNOgrBw","children":[]}]},{"id":"175","parent":"165","text":"3. Productividad\\Nlaboral perdida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"• Costes indirectos: crecimiento económico perdido, cuidadores alejados del mercado laboral.","guid":"VMWzdWKk6JRgZgDGM9aFkg","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"• Coste intangibles: dolor, discapacidad, sufrimiento → valorados en análisis de disposición a pagar.","guid":"DFDraEA71z9VzYI8GuJpng","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"• EE.UU.: 1-3% del PIB atribuible a costes de ECV (mitad relacionada con CI).","guid":"GPStR3XpApNyLtjQYaeFUQ","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"175","text":"• China: coste directo anual de ECV > 40.000 M USD (4% PNB).","guid":"baTlPS1FNd9UDXtGMbgXJw","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"175","text":"• Sudáfrica: 2-3% PNB dedicado al tratamiento de ECV (25% del gasto sanitario).","guid":"S97tqzF_absuDl0pYkVBew","children":[]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"165","text":"4. Costes indirectos\\Nestimados:","guid":"SE8qbnRx9Ps583PcHRTd4w","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"• Diabetes en Latinoamérica y Caribe: costes directos ≈ 10.000 M USD, indirectos ≈ 50.000 M USD (2000).","guid":"DYEeWx93edESBK-nEJI-pA","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"• Obesidad: 2-8% del gasto sanitario en PRA. En India y China, 1,1-2,1% del PIB.","guid":"IlN6LWb4lSoQj4TkBQtI1Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"165","text":"5. Costes por hipertensión\\N(PA alta):","guid":"VxbdkBpZdKNQ62N2Y2fI-A","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"• 2001: coste global de PA alta ≈ 370 M USD (10% del gasto sanitario global).","guid":"WpVL4ia45bJ-SjKWc4n5KQ","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"• Europa oriental: PA alta responsable del 25% del coste sanitario.","guid":"HKHoRXB5C2ZVMX56CkbNgg","children":[]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"165","text":"6. Impacto macroeconómico\\Nen PRMB:","guid":"Hb5BRik--cE7_uSqaZ0u8Q","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"• PRMB como Sudáfrica: ECV afecta al 40% de adultos de 35-64 años (EE.UU.: 10%).","guid":"Wr5jfGoNQdNL4nBsaD-B1w","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"• India y China: mortalidad por ECV en adultos ≈ el doble/triple de la mayoría de los PRA.","guid":"CYS7pV3nIBN40cB7K9g10g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"0","text":"Ética en medicina\\Ncardiovascular","guid":"E_Wz9jb36aotm1DMNOHtQg","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"1. Consentimiento informado:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"192","parent":"191","text":"• Principios éticos: respeto a la autonomía, beneficencia, no maleficencia y justicia.","guid":"GuCxo2xJYrYaS-4MFkI8bA","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"190","text":"• Requisitos:","guid":"U4InaHjp_1hduFVBOzUB_w","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"1. Capacidad de decisión.","guid":"SRhJg3QAmLo7KdBcVplsgA","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"2. Información relevante (alternativas, riesgos, beneficios).","guid":"ba4RIBQtXTtgodVVOAt07g","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"3. Comprensión del paciente.","guid":"bXjU_jFymbQQx_2uVngGQQ","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"4. Decisión voluntaria (sin influencias internas/externas).","guid":"bZbfA2Pc14h7_ZnmTYNyRw","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"193","text":"2. Toma de decisiones compartida\\N(TDC):","guid":"Axvf82CeINQq0_bLMvkB7g","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"• Importante en decisiones complejas (p. ej., dispositivos de asistencia ventricular, DAV).","guid":"HBeyLGl3kcURM9aqNvhjzw","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"• Ayudas para la toma de decisiones → facilitación del diálogo entre paciente y médico.","guid":"VcD0fCt_xLZNOqA7Htk9_w","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"• En pacientes incapaces de decidir, el representante legal debe actuar según juicio de sustitución.","guid":"H4BdcQhkcJh1cqqADS5ukQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"193","text":"3. Juicios éticos de futilidad:","guid":"b4sVKTpTGopWAq5SC6LHVQ","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"• Futilidad fisiológica: intervención no produce desenlace esperado (ej. RCP sin restauración de circulación).","guid":"HJHN01YUf9VFOeOAcBP1Ow","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"• Futilidad inminente-fatal: intervención no evita muerte en ingreso actual.","guid":"Tv5_LiLyOMErSPc6PHdULA","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"• Futilidad de interacción: supervivencia sin capacidad de interacción (ej. estado vegetativo).","guid":"VGTSdTwQ9OgS71puQfuxeA","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"202","text":"• Futilidad de calidad de vida: estado incompatible con la vida significativa para el paciente.","guid":"H-3McA7s9FQPfyO_IwmsZA","children":[]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"193","text":"4. Conflictos de intereses\\N(CDI):","guid":"Y-wJIASe-TYk3_8HMuqITg","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"• Riesgo de que el interés propio influya en el juicio clínico.","guid":"I8qsT2c2hP1CmyskeYugyw","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"• Divulgación de CDI (ej. financieros, asociaciones con industria).","guid":"ErZJsw_Vy2AYZN7LMjanJA","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"207","text":"• Ley Sunshine Act: transparencia en pagos de la industria a médicos.","guid":"GDo7-A3XiUs_ZRW2NMwJyw","children":[]}]},{"id":"211","parent":"193","text":"5. Información pública:","guid":"B8P0LSU0ElEMbAe7K46gfA","children":[{"id":"212","parent":"211","text":"• Evaluación de la calidad de atención médica a través de datos públicos (p. ej., tasas de readmisión hospitalaria).","guid":"J5Ex91Ao9kFvYdx7e_YEbA","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"211","text":"• CMS publica tasas de mortalidad y readmisión ajustadas por riesgo en IAM e insuficiencia cardíaca.","guid":"DDnrKgJRNuk98bXkLCe3mg","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"211","text":"• Riesgo de selección de pacientes para mejorar estadísticas.","guid":"ET4rPU1w2aNPMWP-AMlAZg","children":[]}]},{"id":"215","parent":"193","text":"6. Redes sociales\\Ny salud móvil:","guid":"S1apXhC8ndwr40QDL0Kyfg","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"• Potencial para mejorar la salud pública (ej. grupos de apoyo, aplicaciones móviles).","guid":"DGqXTk8HMuAlGkFIHyDhAQ","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"215","text":"• Riesgos: pérdida de confidencialidad, difamación, violación de privacidad.","guid":"Xtz-QD1_IBNRV4gmdxc6OA","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"193","text":"7. Genética:","guid":"U-BOMXbUg1lZTdwQZR55bg","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"• Medicina personalizada: uso de pruebas genéticas para clasificar pacientes (p. ej., variantes de CYP2C19 y clopidogrel).","guid":"FVuXElDDQwpiLTrNPOzJCQ","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"• Desafíos éticos: manejo de variantes de significado incierto (VSI), derecho a no saber, acceso desigual a pruebas y asesoría genética.","guid":"IOw5TFGPF0g44s11LSYkdg","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"193","text":"8. Big Data:","guid":"TbNSYHJTwZB3l_GlWh3prg","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"• Uso de datos clínicos y HCE en ensayos clínicos → privacidad, consentimiento informado.","guid":"REVc_Ch_QA9l57nVTAlRKQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"193","text":"9. Trasplante:","guid":"W1LwsUMycOxUyq7dcK6Hww","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"• Donación después de muerte circulatoria (DCDMc): debate sobre “irreversibilidad”.","guid":"QVr0cByyMu15PsqvIDfysA","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"223","text":"• Uso de DAV → discusiones previas sobre desactivación si calidad de vida es inaceptable.","guid":"WjFTAEqWUtUXTyzoJYf8Xg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"226","parent":"0","text":"Toma de decisiones clínicas en\\Ncardiología (Brush & Krumholz)","guid":"CIcA8mZ-HkFiCBG4XGdPIw","children":[{"id":"227","parent":"226","text":"1. Razonamiento clínico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"228","parent":"227","text":"• Decisiones basadas en datos médicos + conocimiento del paciente (preferencias, objetivos).","guid":"XVKhmjtV7clBhciRIZf-lg","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"227","text":"• Reglas simplificadas → algorítmicas (p.ej., IAM → AAS, β-bloqueantes).","guid":"Y9Ut2CdtgmZtoU-_MYiAOA","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"227","text":"• Juicio clínico prevalece sobre algoritmos → adaptación a situaciones individuales.","guid":"GcFD92U5QWULpmnmWxw4Zw","children":[]}]},{"id":"231","parent":"226","text":"2. Decisiones diagnósticas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"232","parent":"231","text":"• Clasificación diagnóstica → signos + síntomas.","guid":"Aet0UgTlNJV7VCsYXBzHUw","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"231","text":"• Ej. Disnea + soplo sistólico → sospecha de estenosis aórtica (confirmación con pruebas).","guid":"T3uHaxKjWAABpMOxKs54HA","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"231","text":"• Incertidumbre diagnóstica → insuficiencia cardíaca + otras causas (p.ej., EPOC, neumonía).","guid":"VdXI7FZvco4bfP_gact84w","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"226","text":"3. Decisiones\\Nterapéuticas:","guid":"W0j3RRwiXt5RaRe3dQo7PA","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"• Riesgo vs. Beneficio → evaluación probabilística.","guid":"DWdcOEkYUKwerWolFe5dKg","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"• Estratificación del riesgo → modelos estadísticos (ej. ACC/AHA).","guid":"L5Zu7gC1e95yVaxNDOkQiA","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"235","text":"• Análisis de subgrupos → heterogeneidad de efectos terapéuticos.","guid":"PAtppzPbdN8ugQ8fH-CXfw","children":[]}]},{"id":"239","parent":"226","text":"4. Estrategias de\\Nsolicitud de pruebas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"240","parent":"239","text":"• Hipótesis → pruebas para confirmar/rechazar.","guid":"AVugQ10PgZ1QJnOkA0cUlg","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"239","text":"• Evitar sobreutilización de pruebas → impacto en atención del paciente.","guid":"YfS2Mkt6nrxfY9vpMXA9nQ","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"239","text":"• Criterios de empleo apropiado → guías ACC.","guid":"Xh32vGEIn5pcPrW6M_O_qQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"243","parent":"226","text":"5. Predicción del riesgo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"244","parent":"243","text":"• Herramientas de predicción → manejo preventivo basado en riesgo.","guid":"N3gSKXe7tZodvzyMRN9uYQ","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"243","text":"• Comunicación de riesgo al paciente → uso de pictogramas para facilitar comprensión.","guid":"QNQGRjxsprFazcuMcGp1NA","children":[]}]},{"id":"246","parent":"226","text":"6. Ensayos de no\\Ninferioridad:","guid":"R_bzump3O2xRUh86SVKT_g","children":[{"id":"247","parent":"246","text":"• Comparación de nuevos tratamientos vs. estándar (p.ej., anticoagulantes vs. warfarina).","guid":"PSIij00jd9l9U4W9eS2MNg","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"246","text":"• Margen de inferioridad → impacto clínico (aceptabilidad de reducción de eficacia).","guid":"AP7suCvUlNwZDiO1XEfj_g","children":[]}]},{"id":"249","parent":"226","text":"7. Número necesario\\Na tratar (NNT):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"250","parent":"249","text":"• Evaluación del impacto terapéutico → NNT pequeño = mayor eficacia.","guid":"R4a9CSF4kt5MmaiUKXtzPA","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"249","text":"• Ej. NNT para betabloqueadores post-IAM = 34 → se necesita tratar a 34 pacientes para evitar una muerte.","guid":"bPMxmiv9hH1a67DZSxEoVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"252","parent":"226","text":"8. Falacias en toma\\Nde decisiones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"253","parent":"252","text":"• Juicio apresurado: diagnóstico sin diferencial adecuado.","guid":"DQYkFzcqZpN_BOgARH42QA","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"252","text":"• Juicios sesgados: influencias inconscientes (p.ej. , estereotipos, aversión al riesgo).","guid":"LuYcLRzEJIwJXaSib7oidA","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"252","text":"• Estimaciones distorsionadas de la probabilidad: sobreestimación de eventos improbables.","guid":"WTDLPWQrcC5gJJeoFlLtzQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"256","parent":"0","text":"Medida y mejora de la calidad de la asistencia:\\Nrelevancia para la práctica clínica cardiovascular","guid":"MU7oB114HWUPgHoDMk3UwA","children":[{"id":"257","parent":"256","text":"1. Definición de calidad\\Nde la asistencia","guid":"CUyyQSiOnbkOlbi-UUOl_A","children":[{"id":"258","parent":"257","text":"• Calidad = grado en que los servicios de salud optimizan resultados ➡️ Supervivencia, estado de salud, calidad de vida, morbilidad, experiencia del paciente, rentabilidad.","guid":"EwXZJV_n1_galjn6WoyWLw","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"257","text":"• Institute of Medicine (IOM) (EE.UU.)\\Npropone 6 dominios de calidad:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"260","parent":"259","text":"1. Eficacia","guid":"AWBq12cv4o4ECAlrblOccQ","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"259","text":"2. Seguridad","guid":"Ey1nC17zukQ5ZMTIIDOLIg","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"259","text":"3. Equidad","guid":"Fh4g2DhprMhkscFjRQQ9BQ","children":[]},{"id":"263","parent":"259","text":"4. Puntualidad","guid":"VS3RVG4PZgU0vl95Ll6ckg","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"259","text":"5. Eficiencia","guid":"UjrWMxTi9yJEsYpfA4m-Og","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"259","text":"6. Enfoque en el paciente (1).","guid":"clsUh1QyBGI115L6e6fGyQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"266","parent":"256","text":"2. Relevancia de la calidad en la\\Npráctica cardiovascular","guid":"fMCiG0RtS7hM62zFD8Z7QQ","children":[{"id":"267","parent":"266","text":"• Variación en la calidad ➡️ Infrautilización de tratamientos indicados, sobreutilización de terapias innecesarias, complicaciones y errores médicos\\N➡️ Resultados subóptimos (2).","guid":"JFUjsWeBpr9qUxFwJbWOiA","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"266","text":"• Ej: Diferencias geográficas en EE.UU. en el uso de pruebas e intervenciones cardiovasculares sin mejores resultados (3).","guid":"TrGJTW5bGtsUCSr5Yd7wWA","children":[]}]},{"id":"269","parent":"256","text":"3. Medición de la\\Ncalidad de la asistencia","guid":"TU7VH01t78ICEnt6Y2z19w","children":[{"id":"270","parent":"269","text":"• Tipos de medidas de calidad:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"271","parent":"270","text":"1. Estructura: Atributos específicos del sistema asistencial (volumen de intervenciones, acreditaciones) (4).","guid":"BdecimbEPN0ocTL9WwVt3w","children":[]},{"id":"272","parent":"270","text":"2. Proceso: Acciones de los clínicos (prescripción de medicamentos) respaldadas por guías clínicas (5).","guid":"VNOi4l0vknYJZApxJw55FQ","children":[]},{"id":"273","parent":"270","text":"3. Resultado: Ajuste del riesgo y análisis de resultados en función de intervenciones (6).","guid":"chKJmE4VlNAqmDdQZG2eIA","children":[]},{"id":"274","parent":"270","text":"4. Valor: Integración de calidad y coste (7).","guid":"IkeZMmBvykpgFWTpHwg7Tg","children":[]},{"id":"275","parent":"270","text":"5. Compuestas: Combinación de varios aspectos de calidad (8).","guid":"JN0WAy0A0a4uzraPSTI5tA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"276","parent":"256","text":"4. Fuentes de datos","guid":"FIJ4bRkhx_9u58g8YzQBug","children":[{"id":"277","parent":"276","text":"• Datos de reclamaciones: Utilizados para pagar servicios, con limitaciones clínicas (9).","guid":"B3zi2gLw8zVFEvISVMu3-Q","children":[]},{"id":"278","parent":"276","text":"• Datos clínicos: Más precisos pero más costosos (10).","guid":"UF7i90clbYw4OK3xVjZ_gg","children":[]},{"id":"279","parent":"276","text":"• Registros clínicos: Ej. National Cardiovascular Data Registry (NCDR), Get With the Guidelines (AHA), STS (11).","guid":"LemqamCp4O4xO-1hAr1NTA","children":[]}]},{"id":"280","parent":"256","text":"5. Usos de las\\Nmedidas de calidad","guid":"PdlzZDqf99Ipy8ZiL-v8_Q","children":[{"id":"281","parent":"280","text":"• Mejora de calidad (MC) o Responsabilidad (comunicación pública, pago por rendimiento)\\N➡️ Incentivan mejora en algunos casos (12).","guid":"CLWMolRj_bIUWZsdKv0l1A","children":[]}]},{"id":"282","parent":"256","text":"6. Estrategias de\\Nmejora de la calidad","guid":"NNPH_HRvAAZKBWEiWbDd_w","children":[{"id":"283","parent":"282","text":"• Ciclo PDSA (Plan-Do-Study-Act): Planificación, ejecución, estudio y ajuste de cambios en ciclos repetidos (13).","guid":"IW_RtHjUF7Ei4xezNfJKIQ","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"282","text":"• Lean: Enfoque en eficiencia, reducción de desperdicio (14).","guid":"EfXfsBHK3-8ZJkvbGXLCig","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"282","text":"• Six Sigma: Minimización de errores y variación en procesos asistenciales (15).","guid":"FLvTJV45Pe1uPnqEZRq2HA","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"282","text":"• Lean Six Sigma: Combinación de estrategias Lean y Six Sigma para mejorar eficiencia y reducir errores (16).","guid":"JV6reSZ3KHU7UTWeU0hV4w","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"282","text":"7. Conclusión","guid":"ByEJY2yNIv9WBaMwRPp8xw","children":[{"id":"288","parent":"287","text":"• MC ➡️ Mejora continua de la asistencia ➡️ Mejores resultados para los pacientes.","guid":"Jy0a0X_RaZJ05nnEL-Kncw","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"287","text":"• Implicación activa de los clínicos cardiovasculares en la medición y mejora de la calidad\\Nes fundamental para una asistencia más eficaz, segura y centrada en el paciente (17).","guid":"VDVnRAlAFOFa381ICQkvQA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"290","parent":"0","text":"Evaluación crítica de\\Nensayos clínicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"291","parent":"290","text":"1. Génesis de la pregunta\\Nde investigación","guid":"fa8U5yTlLmpiug1AHx7mmw","children":[{"id":"292","parent":"291","text":"• Uso de criterios FINER para formular\\Npreguntas de investigación adecuadas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"293","parent":"292","text":"F: Factible","guid":"HblGHAWdJPNVETC8L68lzA","children":[]},{"id":"294","parent":"292","text":"I: Interesante","guid":"F2gE4243fJdJIehXLCPYCA","children":[]},{"id":"295","parent":"292","text":"N: Novedosa","guid":"THC6hDdgYtsRPo4kcc9l_g","children":[]},{"id":"296","parent":"292","text":"E: Ética","guid":"XdeLUEyPw8NFF7vhZPiUsw","children":[]},{"id":"297","parent":"292","text":"R: Relevante (1).","guid":"ORzmwhsdXxEp8xF6YEoBlA","children":[]}]},{"id":"298","parent":"291","text":"• Fases en evaluación\\Nde tratamientos:","guid":"Gu7Iox7Ziz8QLKkHbyQv5w","children":[{"id":"299","parent":"298","text":"Fase I: Seguridad ➡️ ¿se puede seguir investigando?","guid":"KBmgIGsMdk94LV8oJci1CA","children":[]},{"id":"300","parent":"298","text":"Fase II: Eficacia, dosis, efectos adversos","guid":"D_GkulrnbGhE55ujLarq1g","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"298","text":"Fase III: Comparación con tratamiento de referencia","guid":"YISRWxn4zGBdWhCid-yWPg","children":[]},{"id":"302","parent":"298","text":"Fase IV: Vigilancia postcomercialización (2).","guid":"CDBI9yZ7-PkkEG5GVKEDfA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"303","parent":"290","text":"2. Diseño del ensayo clínico","guid":"NZ3a0zl9i6pxgaQAN3ybAQ","children":[{"id":"304","parent":"303","text":"• Ensayo clínico aleatorizado\\Ncontrolado (EAC):","guid":"Xdxb1DVO_GtGcGl6O7PnJA","children":[{"id":"305","parent":"304","text":"• Método estándar para evaluar tratamientos ➡️ Reducción de sesgo por aleatorización (3).","guid":"Ad7ALguIJVsgrHvXOvum8A","children":[]},{"id":"306","parent":"304","text":"• Aleatorización fija o adaptativa según las características basales o resultados emergentes (4).","guid":"JqWEbUqfjVIbRaiEQZRNEA","children":[]},{"id":"307","parent":"304","text":"• Ensayo abierto, simple ciego, doble ciego o triple ciego (5).","guid":"aXkYkStyUYwwuHz4EZK4sQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"308","parent":"303","text":"• Tipos de estudios controlados:","guid":"V_FhBwBO3mhzDSIwNc283A","children":[{"id":"309","parent":"308","text":"1. No aleatorizados, con controles concurrentes o históricos.","guid":"Fn7H2yjl3CA3W225JnBslQ","children":[]},{"id":"310","parent":"308","text":"2. Ensayo de grupos cruzados: el paciente es su propio control.","guid":"A81IiHxDCV1UG1drZFHZ4w","children":[]},{"id":"311","parent":"308","text":"3. Ensayos de retirada para estudiar la respuesta a la suspensión de tratamiento (6).","guid":"FjvVvTF1aA5cPnAiHmwetA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"312","parent":"290","text":"3. Tipos de diseño","guid":"RQWxBhIuH9hyeEHya6s1cw","children":[{"id":"313","parent":"312","text":"• Diseño factorial: Comparación de múltiples tratamientos en un\\Núnico ensayo mediante aleatorizaciones independientes (7).","guid":"XM2tKg296nYtP4KDRkbFuw","children":[]},{"id":"314","parent":"312","text":"• Diseño de superioridad\\Ny no inferioridad:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"315","parent":"314","text":"• Ensayo de superioridad: evalúa si el tratamiento es mejor que el control.","guid":"OTA8Al33_3tX2X5sT68D3g","children":[]},{"id":"316","parent":"314","text":"• Ensayo de no inferioridad: evalúa si el tratamiento no es peor que el control dentro de un margen aceptable (8).","guid":"Bt3bmw807CZ2H3BzCqskIw","children":[]},{"id":"317","parent":"314","text":"• Margen de no inferioridad (M) especificado ➡️ Evaluación bioestadística para rechazar H0 y aceptar HA (9).","guid":"C3f1g0o6x99u_P4HIbPLQA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"318","parent":"290","text":"4. Selección del\\Ncriterio de valoración","guid":"e7Av7Us7bilAH-n0U6GQ9A","children":[{"id":"319","parent":"318","text":"• Criterios de valoración compuestos: Agrupamiento de eventos (p.ej., MACE) ➡️ Mayor eficiencia en comparación de efectos (10).","guid":"S4pMkTMtDCUJb03QASgnZQ","children":[]},{"id":"320","parent":"318","text":"• Criterios indirectos (surrogates): Uso de variables intermedias para medir resultados (11).","guid":"bKqXz3rw8dE4pMJmMbBI1Q","children":[]},{"id":"321","parent":"318","text":"• Interpretación del tratamiento: Reducción absoluta de riesgos (RAR) ➡️ NNT (número necesario para tratar) o NND (número necesario para dañar) (12).","guid":"DR8RqSsdBFgdW35Iaey-0w","children":[]}]},{"id":"322","parent":"290","text":"5. Aspectos clave\\Ndurante el ensayo","guid":"ONruz0qbAMwwM4SOcgsq0Q","children":[{"id":"323","parent":"322","text":"• Comité de control de datos y seguridad (CCDS): Monitorea los datos para evaluar si el tratamiento es beneficioso o debe ser detenido (13).","guid":"KJMARwgNAvpBui6vL3Db4w","children":[]},{"id":"324","parent":"322","text":"• Datos perdidos: Esfuerzo para minimizar pérdida de seguimiento y datos incompletos (14).","guid":"F0HvIDfZnyM6HAAGIrnkow","children":[]},{"id":"325","parent":"322","text":"• Análisis de subgrupos: Evaluación cuidadosa para evitar errores en interpretaciones de subgrupos (15).","guid":"AhRnAikY_g1Eba_jfcSW7w","children":[]}]},{"id":"326","parent":"290","text":"6. Fase de análisis","guid":"dFRsNgSNmdhRZifjP964yA","children":[{"id":"327","parent":"326","text":"• Plan de análisis estadístico (PAE): Define cohortes, pruebas estadísticas, y subgrupos de interés para análisis finales (16).","guid":"VcZnhXmropNWFYaiYuV5Lg","children":[]},{"id":"328","parent":"326","text":"• Interacción del tratamiento: Evaluación de riesgos y beneficios ➡️ NNT/NND en diferentes contextos temporales y clínicos (17).","guid":"JMim7HNxBOpM0jgBXaOVuw","children":[]}]},{"id":"329","parent":"290","text":"7. Perspectivas futuras","guid":"N7ql_VrVdbRBBuAtJGU9zA","children":[{"id":"330","parent":"329","text":"• Tendencias futuras en\\Nensayos clínicos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"331","parent":"330","text":"1. Inclusión de pacientes en la planificación de estudios.","guid":"PgwFtn0FvI9PrsCMZp8F_g","children":[]},{"id":"332","parent":"330","text":"2. Uso de historias médicas electrónicas y registros longitudinales para integrar aleatorización.","guid":"BRK_iRFo7zwWD-HhHFSuqg","children":[]},{"id":"333","parent":"330","text":"3. Uso de biomarcadores y diseños adaptativos para mejorar la medicina de precisión (18).","guid":"SUKOX1Ar4ec_DpNNS1b1YQ","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":333,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Estudios Pivotales","folder":"Estudios Pivotales","filename":"BRAUNWALD. 1. Consideraciones generales-2024","id":"map_2470","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"BRAUNWALD. 1. Consideraciones generales-2024"}